# Todo App

A simple Todo list application using Node.js, Express, and MongoDB for the backend, and vanilla HTML, CSS, and JavaScript for the frontend.

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- Node.js
- MongoDB

### Installation

1. Clone the repository:
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/yourusername/my-todo-app.git

2.	Navigate to the backend directory and install dependencies:
    cd my-todo-app/backend
npm install

3.	Start the MongoDB server.
4.	Start the backend server:
    node app.js

5.	Open frontend/index.html in your web browser.
